From: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Jul 2015 09:31:13 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] video: mxc: suppress the overly verbose info message

The mxc driver will poll the cable status per 20 jiffies and print
"same edid" for each poll. This seems pretty verbose and makes no
sense. Make it visible only when debug is enabled.

Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/video/mxc/mxc_hdmi.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/mxc/mxc_hdmi.c b/drivers/video/mxc/mxc_hdmi.c
index 10b54fb..4ed2e77 100644
--- a/drivers/video/mxc/mxc_hdmi.c
+++ b/drivers/video/mxc/mxc_hdmi.c
@@ -1646,7 +1646,7 @@ static int mxc_hdmi_read_edid(struct mxc_hdmi *hdmi)
 	hdmi_set_edid_cfg(&hdmi->edid_cfg);
 
 	if (!memcmp(edid_old, hdmi->edid, HDMI_EDID_LEN)) {
-		dev_info(&hdmi->pdev->dev, "same edid\n");
+		dev_dbg(&hdmi->pdev->dev, "same edid\n");
 		return HDMI_EDID_SAME;
 	}
 
